## ADR-F001 — Next.js + Material-UI + Supabase Frontend Stack

<a id="adr-f001"></a>
**Date**: 2025-08-31  
**Status**: Accepted  
**Owner**: AI Agent

### Context

The frontend needed to be migrated from Firebase to Supabase while maintaining a modern, scalable React application architecture. The application required server-side rendering, real-time features, responsive design, and seamless authentication flows.

### Alternatives

- **Next.js + Firebase + Chakra UI**: Keep existing Firebase but use different UI library
- **Vite + React + Material-UI + Supabase**: Fast build tool but no SSR benefits
- **Next.js + Material-UI + Supabase**: Full-stack framework with comprehensive UI system

### Decision

Implement Next.js 14 + Material-UI + Supabase frontend stack:

**Core Framework:**
- Next.js 14 with App Router for modern React patterns and SSR
- TypeScript throughout for type safety
- Material-UI (MUI) v5 for comprehensive component library
- Supabase JavaScript client for database and auth integration

**Architecture Patterns:**
- **Component-First Design**: Reusable React components with Material-UI foundation
- **Real-time Integration**: Supabase real-time subscriptions for live data updates
- **Theme System**: Consistent design system with Material-UI theming
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with MUI breakpoint system
- **Authentication Context**: React Context for auth state management
- **API Integration**: Direct Supabase client calls and FastAPI backend integration

**Development Experience:**
- Hot reload development with Next.js
- Comprehensive component library with MUI
- Built-in accessibility features
- TypeScript integration throughout
- Real-time development feedback

### Consequences

- **Pros**: Modern React patterns, comprehensive UI system, excellent developer experience, built-in accessibility, server-side rendering benefits, real-time capabilities
- **Cons**: Learning curve for Next.js App Router, Material-UI styling patterns, larger bundle size than minimal solutions
- **Supersedes**: Legacy Firebase-based frontend ADRs (002-009 from previous template)
- **Superseded by**: —

### Compliance / Verification

All frontend components use Material-UI as foundation. Next.js App Router patterns implemented throughout. Supabase client properly integrated for auth and data. TypeScript strict mode enabled. Responsive design verified across breakpoints.
